<TITLE> Controversial Nepal crown prince leaves hospital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KATHMANDU, Sept 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Nepal's controversial Crown Prince Paras, a lightning rod for criticism of the monarchy because of his playboy image, was discharged from hospital on Wednesday after suffering a heart attack last week, doctors said. The 35-year-old prince, known for drunken brawls in discos, was rushed to the Norvic hospital on Thursday. Doctors then said the heart attack was related to Paras' fast lifestyle. "He has gone to his residence ... His condition is very good," Dr Shyam Bahadur Pandey, who was involved in the treatment of the prince, said. The prince would be under medical supervision for three weeks. Paras is the only son of King Gyanendra who ascended the throne after the 2001 palace massacre in which popular King Birendra and most other royals were killed by then Crown Prince Dipendra, who later turned the gun on himself. The monarchy faces an uncertain future in the religious nation which is due to hold elections on Nov. 22 for a special assembly which will map the country's political future including that of the monarc
